Got it — batching the remaining steps. You're past the dialog-juggling part; the rest is sequential and you can rip through it.

Step 5 — Save the table
Click Save at the bottom of the New table dialog.
Wait for the table to finish creating (15-30 seconds; you'll see a spinner, then land on the table's editor page with tabs like Columns, Relationships, Forms, Views).

Step 6 — Add the BU Code column
In the table editor, click the Columns area → + New column.
BU Code
Description:
Short code identifying the business unit (e.g. "FIN", "HR", "ENG"). Must be unique across all BUs.
Data type: Single line of text
Maximum character count:
10
Required: Business required
Click Save.

Step 7 — Add the Status column
Click + New column again.
Status
Description:
Whether the BU is currently active and selectable for assignment to apps/CPs/BPs.
Data type: Choice
Sync this choice with: select New choice (creates a fresh choice, not a global one)
Choice items — add exactly these two, in this order:
Item 1:

Label: Active
Value: 890920000

Item 2:

Label: Inactive
Value: 890920001

Default choice: Active
Required: Business required
After the choice is created, look for the Schema name under Advanced options and manually edit it to:
bustatus
(So the full logical name becomes pei_bustatus, not pei_status — this avoids the ADR-034 anti-pattern.)
Click Save.

Step 8 — Add the Parent BU column (self-lookup)
Click + New column.
Parent BU
Description:
The parent business unit in the BU hierarchy. Root BUs (top of hierarchy) have no parent. Self-referential lookup.
Data type: Lookup
Related table: Business Unit (this same table — it'll appear in the dropdown since the table now exists)
Required: Optional (root BUs need to allow null parent)
Under Advanced options, set the Schema name to:
parentbu
(So logical becomes pei_parentbu.)
Click Save.

Step 9 — Enable Hierarchical on the Parent BU relationship
After saving the Parent BU column, you need to mark its underlying relationship as hierarchical.

In the table editor, click the Relationships area (left nav of the table)
Find the relationship pei_businessunit_pei_parentbu (or similarly named — it'll be the self-referential one created when you added Parent BU)
Open it
Look for a checkbox or toggle labeled Hierarchical — check it
Save the relationship

If you don't see "Hierarchical" as an option in the modern UI, it's reachable via the classic Solution Explorer (make.powerapps.com → Settings → "Switch to classic" if you have access). Tell me if you can't find it and I'll route you the long way.

Step 10 — Add the Alternate Key on BU Code
Still in the table editor, click the Keys area (it may be under "Schema" in the left nav, or as a separate sub-tab).
Click + New key.
BU Code Unique
Columns: select BU Code (only column — single-field key)
Click Save.
